<p>I'm trying to dedupe a data set and convert the dedupe dataset to another data frame . However the deduped dataset has the first column as group by variables</p>  <pre><code>import pandas as pd df = pd.DataFrame({ 'Cust':list('AAABBB'),'PA1':list('HHHMMH'),                     'PA2': list('MLMMMM'),'PA3':[1,2,3,3,3,1] })  df2 = df.groupby('Cust').sum()  for col in ['PA1','PA2','PA3']:     df2[col] = df.groupby('Cust')[col].apply( lambda x:                                                '&amp;'.join( x.astype(str).unique() )) </code></pre>  <p>This gives me output (df2) as </p>  <pre><code>        PA3  PA1  PA2 Cust                  A     1&amp;2&amp;3    H  M&amp;L B       3&amp;1  M&amp;H    M </code></pre>  <p>I want the output copied to another data frame (df3) to display as  (preserve the column order of the original dates- df) The reason is the deduduped dataelements needs to loaded to a database and the layout (column order)  of the original (and the db schema) and deduped dataset should be same. </p>  <pre><code>Cust   PA1    PA2 PA3 A     1&amp;2&amp;3    H  M&amp;L B     3&amp;1  M&amp;H    M </code></pre>  <p>Thanks PMV</p>